This paper deals with wireless networks and interference management, which are topics that fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of OFDMA and resource allocation also suggests that Information Theory (cs.IT) may be relevant. The mention of fading fluctuations and precoding indicates that Multimedia (cs.MM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the interactions and trade-offs between different strategies, which suggests that Computer Communications and Networks (cs.COM) may also be a relevant sub-category.
